{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Place water, sugar and yeast in mixing bowl then warm <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl with oil.","Add buttermilk, flour and salt then knead <nobr>3 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to prepared bowl, cover with cling film then set aside to rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1-2 hours). Clean mixing bowl and prepare topping."]},{"title":"Topping","content":["Place Parmesan and Fontina cheese in mixing bowl then grate <nobr>8 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place mozzarella in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to bowl with other cheeses then set aside.","Towards end of rising time, preheat oven to 220°C and line a large baking tray with baking paper. Tip dough out onto a floured work surface and roll out to size of baking tray (approx. 1 cm deep). Transfer pizza base to prepared baking tray.","Scatter reserved chopped cheeses and gorgonzola over dough then sprinkle with pepper. Bake for 15-20 minutes (220°C) until bubbling and golden. Serve pizza hot, cut in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["50 g water","1 tsp sugar","2 tsp dried instant yeast","oil, for greasing","180 g buttermilk","400 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for flouring","1 tsp fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (3 cm)","50 g Fontina cheese, cut in pieces (3 cm)","80 g mozzarella, drained, cut in pieces","80 g gorgonzola, cut in pieces (5 mm)","1 pinch ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r131863","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-7Sn8OabExt8\/XZan011-vWI\/AAAAAAAAhEU\/xqivENep-EUipW-9UGS-E8X8Pduw33ArwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Vf2ID-evqCHpKd3z.png","title":"Four Cheese Pizza","publishedAt":"2016-09-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"30 g","fat":"17.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"80.1 g","calories":"2431 kJ \/ 581 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, cling film, rolling pin, large baking tray, baking paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To make a closed cheese pizza, divide dough in half and roll out 2 thin rectangles (one slightly larger than then the other). Place largest piece in baking tray, spread cheese over then cover with second piece of dough. Cook as directed in recipe.","Use cheeses of your choice as alternatives to the ones listed in the recipe.","Try adding herbs (e.g. thyme or marjoram).","This is a traditional Italian four cheese pizza, made without a tomato sauce."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","2h 35m","4 portions"]}